I"¶<h2 id="timeline">Timeline</h2>

<ul>
  <li>End of Week 2: Students begin brainstorming project ideas individually using the following guidelines.</li>
  <li>Week 3: Students share their project ideas and vote on which projects they would like to work on.</li>
  <li>End of Week 3: Students choose their preference among the most popular projects</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="project-template">Project Template</h3>

<p>Fill out the following template for your project idea.</p>

<div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="gu">### [Project Title]</span>

<span class="gu">### Pitch</span>

2 - 3 sentences that explains what the application will do.

<span class="gu">### Features</span>
<span class="p">
*</span> What features will your app include?

<span class="gu">### Integrations</span>
<span class="p">
*</span> Which APIs will you use?
<span class="p">*</span> Which OAuth integration are you planning to use?
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="apis">APIs</h3>

<p>Your application <strong>must make good use of one external dataset or API</strong>. Some examples include:</p>

<h4 id="government-data">Government Data</h4>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.data.gov/">Data.gov</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://www.propublica.org/tools/">ProPublica</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://data.nasa.gov/api-info/">NASA</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://www.census.gov/data/developers/data-sets.html">US Census</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://opendata.socrata.com/dataset/Socrata-Customer-Spotlights/6wk3-4ija">Socrata Listings</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://www.bls.gov/developers/api_ruby.htm">Bureau of Labor &amp; Statistics</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.undata-api.org/">United Nations</a> (3rd party API)</li>
  <li><a href="http://www.google.com/publicdata/directory">Googleâ€™s Directory of Public Data</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://data.opencolorado.org/">OpenColorado</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://drcog.org/services-and-resources/data-maps-and-modeling">Denver Regional Council of Governments</a></li>
</ul>

<h4 id="corporate-data">Corporate Data</h4>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://dev.twitter.com">Twitter</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://developers.facebook.com">Facebook</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://instagram.com/developer">Instagram</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://developer.github.com/v3">Github</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://dev.fitbit.com">FitBit</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://developer.spotify.com/web-api">Spotify</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.strava.com/developers">Strava</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://developers.google.com/maps">Google Maps</a></li>
</ul>

<h4 id="featurestechnologies">Features/Technologies</h4>

<ul>
  <li>SMS messaging</li>
  <li>Email</li>
  <li>Optical Character Recognition (OCR)</li>
  <li>Natural Language Processing (NLP)</li>
  <li>Machine Learning</li>
  <li>Data Analytics</li>
  <li>Websockets</li>
  <li>Messaging Brokers/Queues</li>
  <li>Data Visualization</li>
  <li>Location Services (Google Maps/Directions)</li>
  <li>IOT Hardware (ex: Raspberry PI)</li>
</ul>

<p>However, the list is not limited to these. You can choose to integrate with a service of your choosing, as long as it is approved by your client.</p>
